        "title": "Flip (Mirror) Image Java",
        "body": "<p>I'm trying to mirror or flip an image but my code only mirrors half the image and I don't know how to fix it. This is the original image:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/eRE6G.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">original image<\/a>\nI'm trying to get this as my final result:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/By0aS.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">flipped/mirrored image<\/a><\/p>\n<p>I also want to clarify that I know I can take advantage of 2DGraphics and the API support but I'm trying to figure out how I can mirror the image by manipulating the 2D array<\/p>\n<p>This is my code and the result that I get:<\/p>\n<pre><code>public static void applyMirror(BufferedImage img) {\nint width = img.getWidth();\nint height = img.getHeight();\nfor(int j = 0; j &lt; height; j++){\n  for(int i = 0, w = width - 1; i &lt; width; i++, w--){\n    int p = img.getRGB(i, j);\n    img.setRGB(w, j, p);\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/9KIkB.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">my result<\/a><\/p>\n",
