            "creation_date": 1698883275,
            "body": "<p>Simply make use of the available API support.  A really simple trick is to simply scale the image using a negative value in the axis you want mirrored, for example...<\/p>\n<pre><code>BufferedImage mirrored = new BufferedImage(width, height, BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_ARGB);\nGraphics2D g2d = mirrored.createGraphics();\ng2d.scale(-1, 1);\ng2d.translate(-source.getWidth(), 0);\ng2d.drawImage(source, 0, 0, null);\ng2d.dispose();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Not only is it faster, it's also a lot simpler<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/DO8mg.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/DO8mg.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /><\/a><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KEspA.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KEspA.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /><\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 77406242,
            "question_id": 77406128
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Z2KYN.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 960307,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 984823,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/984823/joop-eggen",
                "reputation": 110397,
                "display_name": "Joop Eggen"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1698892894,
            "creation_date": 1698881972,
            "body": "<p>You have to walk for i upto width/2.\nOtherwise you swap every (i, width - i - 1) twice. ;)<\/p>\n<p>And swap the two opposite pixels.<\/p>\n<p>\u2013-----<\/p>\n<h2>Code<\/h2>\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0, w = width - 1; i &lt; w; ++i, --w) {\n    int pi = img.getRGB(i, j);\n    int pw = img.getRGB(w, j);\n    img.setRGB(i, j, pw);\n    img.setRGB(w, j, pi);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>This ensures you do not write an already changed pixel, as your code did.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 77406190,
            "question_id": 77406128,
            "last_edit_date": 1698892894
        }
